<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1089,280,446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Material (deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[442,500,280,301]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">IBER</collectionCode>
): 
<collectingCountry box="[516,615,280,301]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">GREECE</collectingCountry>
: 
<quantity box="[625,663,280,302]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
, Slavyanka (Orvilos) Mts, near Akladohori village, 
<geoCoordinate box="[268,383,309,330]" degrees="41.3200" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" precision="5" value="41.32">N 41.3200°</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[393,503,309,331]" degrees="23.5658" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" precision="5" value="23.5658">E 23.5658°</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[513,575,309,331]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.91" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="591.0">591 m</quantity>
a.s.l., 05.09– 
<date box="[707,816,309,331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2019-10-15">15.10.2019</date>
, pitfall traps, lgt. 
<collectionCode box="[1000,1025,309,330]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
. Naumova; habitat: grassland, with bushes (
<taxonomicName box="[550,702,338,359]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[550,702,338,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Prunus spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode box="[708,725,338,359]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. and 
<taxonomicName box="[781,864,338,359]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[781,828,338,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Rosa</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
) and single oak trees (
<taxonomicName box="[144,289,367,388]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerris">
<emphasis box="[144,289,367,388]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Quercus cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode box="[298,316,367,388]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
.) between cultivated fields and vineyards; 
<quantity box="[777,812,366,388]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
, Sharlia Mts, near Sidirokastro, 
<geoCoordinate box="[214,330,395,417]" degrees="41.2581" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" precision="5" value="41.2581">N 41.2581°</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[339,449,395,417]" degrees="23.4137" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" precision="5" value="23.4137">E 23.4137°</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[459,521,395,417]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.19" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="219.0">219 m</quantity>
a.s.l., 06.06- 
<date box="[647,758,395,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2019-07-08">07.08.2019</date>
, pitfall traps, lgt. 
<collectionCode box="[942,967,396,417]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
. Naumova, habitat: stone pit with scarce vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1089,483,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
This species is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[628,733,483,509]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and North 
<collectingCountry box="[889,1026,483,509]" name="Macedonia" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode pageId="2" pageNumber="65">LAZAROV</collectionCode>
2006, 
<bibRefCitation author="STEFANOVSKA, D. &amp; NAUMOVA, M. &amp; PRELIK, D. &amp; DELTSHEV, C. &amp; LAZAROV, S." box="[295,593,516,543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="35 - 49" refId="ref5916" refString="STEFANOVSKA, D., NAUMOVA, M., PRELIK, D., DELTSHEV, C. &amp; LAZAROV, S. (2008): Spiders from the Skopje region: a faunistic and zoogeographical analysis. - Historia Naturalis Bulgarica 19: 35 - 49." type="journal article" year="2008">
STEFANOVSKA 
<emphasis box="[466,517,516,542]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BLAGOEV, G. &amp; DELTSHEV, C. &amp; LAZAROV, S. &amp; NAUMOVA, M." box="[608,854,516,542]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" refId="ref3680" refString="BLAGOEV, G., DELTSHEV, C., LAZAROV, S. &amp; NAUMOVA, M. (2018): The spiders (Araneae) of Bulgaria. [Internet] Version: August 2018. National Museum of Natural History, Bulgarian Academy of Sciences. Available at http: // www. nmnhs. com / spiders-bulgaria / [accessed on 20.08.2020]" type="url" year="2018">
BLAGOEV 
<emphasis box="[724,783,516,542]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The new records in 
<collectingCountry box="[169,254,550,576]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Greece</collectingCountry>
are expected since the respective sites are located very close to the borders of both countries (
<figureCitation box="[464,550,583,610]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[212,248,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[177,1124,876,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-243@9.[177,1124,876,1530]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 27. Map with the localities of the new faunistic records in the Balkan Peninsula" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734825" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734825/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
